.topic>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.cartonionline.com/gif/CARTOON/disney/re_leone/re_leone07.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Is Epic Worth It??</span><hr size=1> Okay our guild alliance has 6 warriors all working on in line for their Epic. Many of us in the same place, I just dropped to last in line cause I had to work and missed the PoS raid this weekend. <!--EZCODE FONT START--><span style="color:red;font-size:small;">Is the Epic Worth it?</span><!--EZCODE FONT END-->  <br>
<br>
I have heard arguments for and against the Epic but none of the comments have actually been from high level warriors. <!--EZCODE FONT START--><span style="color:red;font-size:small;">Any opinions?</span><!--EZCODE FONT END--> <p><!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>JD aka Little Dove<!--EZCODE BR START--><br /><!--EZCODE BR END-->Doc's Pet Tank<br>
Mighty Mite of Giliath Lang</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--><br>
&quot;Aggroing the mob on a MT is not just the MT's job.<!--EZCODE BR START--><br /><!--EZCODE BR END--> It's everyone's, Tiejinnie: 65 Overlord&quot;<!--EZCODE BR START--><br /><!--EZCODE BR END--><!--EZCODE BR START--><br /><!--EZCODE BR END--><!--EZCODE BR START--><br /><!--EZCODE BR END--><br>
<!--EZCODE CENTER START--><div style="text-align:center"><!--EZCODE IMAGE START--><img src="http://members.cox.net/drjo/jodigari.jpg"/><!--EZCODE IMAGE END--><!--EZCODE BR START--><br /><!--EZCODE BR END--><!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>Doc &amp; Joddi</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
<!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://members.cox.net/drjo/jodigari.html">The Two of Us</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--></div><!--EZCODE CENTER END--></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/bthesteelwarrior.showUserPublicProfile?gid=joddie>Joddie</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://members.cox.net/drjo/heart.gif" BORDER=0> at: 12/19/02 6:22:57 am<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2F2F4F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/bthesteelwarrior.showUserPublicProfile?gid=iskandaralazeem>Iskandar Alazeem</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Guardian of the Battlefield</BR>STEEL WARRIOR Moderator</span><br>  Posts: 1046<br> <font color=#FF0000>(12/16/02 5:13:05 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthebunker.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=4665.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Is Epic Worth It??</span><hr size=1> It's a good weapon for the level of power it requires to earn. Even after scoring a weapon like a SoD, BBotE, or 1 EB weapon, quite a few high level warriors still use the red epic in the offhand until high-aggro 2hs or dual EB weapons are obtained.<br>
<br>
6 warriors is a long line to outfit, though. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/bthesteelwarrior.showUserPublicProfile?gid=shikariiapoccalypse>Shikarii Apoccalypse</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>All in the reflexes</BR>Guardian of the Bunker</BR>STEEL WARRIOR Moderator</span><br>  Posts: 2183<br> <font color=#FF0000>(12/16/02 5:38:39 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthebunker.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=4665.topic&index=2>Reply</a>    <br>ezSupporter<br> <BR><img src=http://www.wingkong.net/Images/minijak.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Is Epic Worth It??</span><hr size=1> I thought my epic was worth it; in a roleplaying and combat oriented situation. Old Shikarii was in a few TOVN drops; full SS..the epic still fit the big picture.<br>
<br>
when you get to the EB-grade weapon drops; sure, the epic loses it's flavor...Until than you'll be hard pressed to find a more useful weapon that carries a 1H and 2H weapon role. Blue blade was a mini-ATK boost+dex, red blade was a +hate proc; 2H was decent DPS andbig boom proc.<br>
<br>
Plus..It was crafted by Rallos Zek himself. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :D --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/happy.gif ALT=":D"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p><!--EZCODE CENTER START--><div style="text-align:center"><!--EZCODE IMAGE START--><img src="http://publish.hometown.aol.com/crushr85/myhomepage/max.jpg" style="border:0;"/><!--EZCODE IMAGE END--></div><!--EZCODE CENTER END--></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2F2F4F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/bthesteelwarrior.showUserPublicProfile?gid=mikilualot>MikilUalot</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>knows that Warriors are superior</span><br>  Posts: 80<br> <font color=#FF0000>(12/16/02 8:32:54 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthebunker.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=4665.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://worldzone.net/ss/DallasKnight/mencasey.JPG WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Is Epic Worth It??</span><hr size=1> Other than the fact that the epic will be a weapon upgrade for me, what makes it more worth it is the time i have put into it. I started my epic at lvl 20 getting the hilts, collecting the gems...basicly doing all the &quot;leg work&quot; now I'm lvl 56 and all i need is the green scale. Yeah camping sev bites the big one, but that will make it just that much MORE worth it whe i finish.  <p><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=42722"><!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>Mikil Vaevictus</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--></a><!--EZCODE LINK END--><!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong> ,Elder of <!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.shadowsight.com/banesidhe/">Bane sidhe</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--></strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><!--EZCODE BR START--><br /><!--EZCODE BR END-->56 Leezard Warrior<!--EZCODE BR START--><br /><!--EZCODE BR END--><!--EZCODE HR START--><hr /><!--EZCODE HR END--><!--EZCODE CENTER START--><div style="text-align:center">Lo, there do I see my father.<!--EZCODE BR START--><br /><!--EZCODE BR END--> Lo, there do I see my mother and my sisters and my brothers.<!--EZCODE BR START--><br /><!--EZCODE BR END--> Lo, there do I see the line of my people, back to the beginning.<!--EZCODE BR START--><br /><!--EZCODE BR END--> Lo, they do call to me...they bid me take my place among them, in the halls of Vallhalla where the brave may live forever.</div><!--EZCODE CENTER END--></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/bthesteelwarrior.showUserPublicProfile?gid=grobsmash>Grobsmash</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>is a Seasoned Veteran</span><br>  Posts: 269<br> <font color=#FF0000>(12/16/02 10:45:36 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthebunker.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=4665.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.oscarpie.com/smiley/lsvader.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Is Epic Worth It??</span><hr size=1> I think it is very worth it.  The only way I think it would not be worth it is if you are in a guild that is pharming EB weapons. <p><!--EZCODE IMAGE START--><img src="http://junipuretruthseeker.homestead.com/files/Semi_final_sig.jpg" style="border:0;"/><!--EZCODE IMAGE END--><br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=36998"> Grobsmash 61 </a><!--EZCODE LINK END--> <!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://pub14.ezboard.com/bthesteelwarrior"> Warlord </a><!--EZCODE LINK END--><br>
<!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.guildportal.com/Guild.asp?GuildID=3066&amp;TabID=21306"> Serendipitous Existence </a><!--EZCODE LINK END--><br>
<!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://pub13.ezboard.com/bprexus95980"> Prexus </a><!--EZCODE LINK END--></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2F2F4F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/bthesteelwarrior.showUserPublicProfile?gid=yaldatindetinytank>Yaldatin Detinytank</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>knows that Warriors are superior</span><br>  Posts: 69<br> <font color=#FF0000>(12/16/02 10:53:33 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthebunker.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=4665.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.nuggett.net/images/barpic.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Is Epic Worth It??</span><hr size=1> Yes,  unless your in a guild that can easily get you better agro weapons.  Or &quot;Pass Down&quot;  a Blade of Carnage then the Red Blade alone is worth it. <br>
<br>
I use Shadowheart (from UP) and Red Blade. My guild got our first ever shot at the AoW  last week and  took him down about a quarter before all hell broke loose. <br>
<br>
We have now refined our  strat  and  should do much better next time. Now that we have experienced this and know better what to expect. So we may  actually be close to our first BoC,  if we can beat  the other 10 or 12 AoW  capable guilds from all over the world who play on the nameless server to Kael, when the statue pops. And  the AoW happens to have one. And all hell does not break loose again. <br>
<br>
I mention when the Statue pops because   most  guilds who kill the statue  go on to Idol and AoW. <p><center>
